File: platform/mcp-server/src/browser-tools/analyze-site/index.ts

The inner catch block (around lines 954-962) for the getNetworkRequests failure currently does:
```
catch {
  try {
    await dispatchToExtension(state, 'browser.disableNetworkCapture', { tabId });
  } catch { }
  state.activeNetworkCaptures.delete(tabId);
}
```

But the outer finally block (around lines 1032-1044) ALSO does:
```
finally {
  try {
    await dispatchToExtension(state, 'browser.disableNetworkCapture', { tabId });
  } catch { }
  state.activeNetworkCaptures.delete(tabId);
}
```

Fix: Remove the disableNetworkCapture call and activeNetworkCaptures.delete from the inner catch. The catch block should only set networkRequests = [] (or just let the empty default stand). The finally block handles all cleanup paths.
